                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d223">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">845.00/1844: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">William Phillips</persName>,
                        Personal Representative of President Roosevelt in India, to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New Delhi</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-03-03T18:00:00+06:30"
                            >March 3, 1943—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 8:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>202. Reference my 191, February 7 [<hi rend="italic">27</hi>], midnight [<hi
                        rend="italic">noon</hi>].<note n="29" xml:id="d223fn29">Not printed.</note>
                    Gandhi ended his fast this morning at 10:30 a.m. The Home Department of the
                    Government of India issued the following communiqué: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“On the termination of Mr. Gandhi’s fast, the arrangements for his
                            detention and that of the other persons detained at the Aga Khan’s
                            Palace which obtained before the fast have now been resumed. Such extra
                            medical assistance and nursing as may be necessary will continue for the
                            present. [”]</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
